    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Guru of Small Things</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Steven A Ludsin letter on James Bennet's June 18 article holds Mark Penn may have found sensible means to represent allAmericans2</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I was intrigued with James Bennet's article (June 18). Mark Penn's ability to connect proposals to values is common sense. The ability to tack on slivers of the electorate to the base vote can make the difference between victory and defeat. Doing little things, with the government as facilitator, is a useful means of accomplishing public policy. A candidate is supposed to represent all of us, and it sounds as if Penn has figured out a sensible means to do it.</p>
        <p>Steven A. Ludsin  New York</p>
      </block>
